OL,3,CFire service watch manager admits
OL,4,Cusing racial slurs against black
OL,5,Ccolleague
OL,7,FUnder his command was a black
OL,8,Ffirefighter who Teesside Crown Court
OL,9,Fheard on Thursday (24 July) was
OL,10,Frepeatedly subjected to highly
OL,11,Foffensive racial slurs by Suggitt
OL,12,Fbetween October 2019 and August 2021.
OL,14,FOn one occasion, a jury heard he used
OL,15,Fthe station's tannoy system to call
OL,16,Fthe firefighter a deeply offensive
OL,17,Fracial slur before adding: "Make my
OL,18,Fcoffee."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/4
