OL,3,CFire service watch manager admits
OL,4,Cusing racial slurs against black
OL,5,Ccolleague
OL,7,FThe prosecution also said that the
OL,8,Fdefendant sent offensive messages to a
OL,9,Fstaff Whatsapp group, which together
OL,10,Fwith the spoken slurs, "crossed a line
OL,11,Ffrom harmless banter".
OL,13,FSuggitt, of Brook Lane, Whitby,
OL,14,Foriginally pleaded not guilty to a
OL,15,Fsingle charge of racially aggravated
OL,16,Fharassment on the grounds that it was
OL,17,Fmeant in fun.
